SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1117
By White
A RESOLUTION to honor Dr. Sidney A. McPhee on the occasion
of his retirement as president of Middle
Tennessee State University.
WHEREAS, Dr. Sidney A. McPhee, the tenth president of Middle Tennessee State
University (MTSU), has presided over one of the most remarkable periods of growth and
progress in the institution's more than 110 years of service; and
WHEREAS, Dr. McPhee is retiring from the presidency in December 2026 after more
than twenty-five years of distinguished service to the university; after taking a two-semester
sabbatical, he will join the College of Education as a tenured professor; and
WHEREAS, since Dr. McPhee's presidency began in 2001, MTSU has been successful
in completing almost $2 billion in improvements in academic, athletic, and campus facilities,
including the School of Concrete and Construction Management, Academic Classroom Building
for the College of Behavioral and Health Sciences, Science Corridor of Innovation, Applied
Engineering Building, and Stephen and Denise Smith Student-Athlete Performance Center; and
WHEREAS, as the leader of Tennessee's largest locally governed university, Dr.
McPhee has solidified and enhanced MTSU's reputation for offering the greatest return on
investment in Tennessee higher education as the top provider of college graduates to the
greater Nashville economy; the third-largest producer of college graduates in the State; and a
destination of choice for first-generation students and transfer students; and
WHEREAS, during Dr. McPhee's presidency, MTSU has been successful in raising
admission standards, resulting in an increase in enrollment of high-ability students, and he has
overseen the addition of some fifty undergraduate and graduate degree programs, two colleges,
and twenty institutes and centers; and
SJR1117
017784
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Dr. McPhee has strengthened MTSU's international initiatives on the
Murfreesboro campus and abroad through forty university partnerships in seventeen different
countries and the enrollment of more international students than any other university in the
State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Dr. McPhee earned his bachelor's degree from Prairie View A&M
University, graduating summa cum laude; a master's degree from the University of Miami, Coral
Gables, Florida; and a doctorate in applied behavioral studies in education from Oklahoma
State University; and
WHEREAS, his work as an academic has appeared in numerous local, national, and
international professional journals; his scholarly pursuits include international lectures and
presentations in numerous countries, including China, Japan, South Korea, Israel, Belgium,
Canada, England, Brazil, Ethiopia, Kenya, and the Bahamas; and
WHEREAS, Dr. McPhee was recently elected to a third term on the NCAA Division I
Board of Directors, representing Conference USA; he has previously served on the NCAA
Executive Committee; and
WHEREAS, Dr. McPhee has received numerous awards and accolades during his
exemplary career; he was named Outstanding American University President by the American
Football Foundation in 2002 and honored among Tennessee's 100 Most Powerful People by the
Nashville Post in 2003 and the State's Top 50 Most Powerful African Americans by Business
Tennessee in 2004; and
WHEREAS, Dr. McPhee was married to his wife, retired educator Elizabeth McPhee, for
forty-five years before her passing and has two adult children, Dr. Seneca McPhee and Dr.
Sidney-Anthony McPhee; and
- 2 - 017784

WHEREAS, for more than a quarter-century, Dr. Sidney McPhee has worked to continue
the progress and success of Middle Tennessee State University as its president, a position he
humbly calls "the great honor of my professional life"; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Dr. Sidney A. McPhee on the occasion of
his retirement as president of Middle Tennessee State University, thank him for more than
twenty-five years of dedicated service to the university, and extend to him our best wishes for
continued success in his future academic endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
